cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.MA, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with proof-search algorithms and automated counter-model extraction for a class of STIT logics, which is a logical formalism. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses automated reasoning and proof-search algorithms, which are common topics in AI. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper introduces a new class of cut-free complete labelled sequent calculi for multi-agent STIT with at most n-many choices, which could be relevant to programming language design. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is another possibility as the paper deals with multi-agent STIT logics and introduces a new class of calculi for them. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the admissibility of structural rules in the refined calculi, which could be relevant to software engineering.
